the set up vs. the shot 🧪⏬

I wanted a Great Gatsby vibe. An over-the-top celebratory feeling, with flares and atmosphere glasses overflowing with ginger ale splashing everywhere to fill the frame. 

Once we got the framing and lighting down we practiced the pour bc we only had one chance to get it right. 

How’d we do?

Photographer @bronson.photo and stylist @sarahk_stylist teamed up to create this campy campaign for @drinkolipop 🥂🛩️

Bronson was heavily involved in the creative of this project and created all five over-the-top characters, brought to life by Sarah’s unique costume design and styling. Together they build a glamorous jet age world so we can all be ‘sippin in first class’ ✨

#olipop #greatbowery

🛩️buckle up🛩️

Thanks for having me @drinkolipop I’ll launch your products any day 😘🛩️

This campaign came together beautifully and I’m so proud to share this work👨🏽‍✈️

With the new year a few days away, we are looking forward to welcoming many new members to The One Club family in 2024. January is a time for reflection and renewal, and as we look toward our goals for the year, we would love for you to be a part of them.

Bronson, an accomplished Black Filipino Photographer and Director, stands out for his outgoing nature and exceptional talent. A proud member of the queer community, he uses his art to create visual impact, emphasizing the representation of LGBTQIA+, POC, and AAPI individuals.

Bronson’s contributions go beyond his lens—he served on the Young Guns 20 Jury and earned recognition in ADC 2023, showcasing his commitment to the industry. In a recent interview, he shared insights into his journey, emphasizing the importance of showing up, trying, and building a supportive community.

As we continue the holiday season, The One Club is thrilled to offer a limited-time 20% discount on Memberships. Join our creative community
